<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-175-754  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 175 754.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 19 1990 n355 p75(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multimedia aids public. (IBM's M-Motion Video Adapter/A card andM-Control Program software utilized in public informationretrieval system) (Hillsboro County, Fla's 24-hour City Hallprogram) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harrington, Maura J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A pilot project called the 24-hour City Hall in Hillsboro County,Fl, utilizes the IBM M-Motion Video Adapter/A graphics board andits M-Control Program software toolkit.andP;  Using the IBM multimediasystem, Hillsboro County officials have created a video-basedinformation retrieval system that enables citizens to accessinformation on a range of available county services.andP;  The pilot ispart of a nationwide project organized by IBM and PublicTechnology Inc, the research branch of the National League ofCities.andP;  The system utilizes real-time video, graphics and text.andO;It gives multimedia capabilities to IBM PS/2 Micro Channel Model50 computer systems or higher.andP;  The card and software kit will becommercially available in April 1990 at $2,250 and $150respectively.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM M-Motion Video Adapter/A (Graphics board) (usage)M-Control Program (Computer program) (usage).andO;Topic:     Pilot ProjectsGraphics Boards-CardsInformation SystemsMultimedia SoftwareBeta TestingCounty Government.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>